<HEADLINE> Pudong Development Bank Moves Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Pudong Development Bank
officially moved its headquarters today to one of the oldest bank
buildings on Shanghai famous Bund, the building formerly occupied
by the Shanghai Branch of Hong Kong and Shanghai Bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank's first day of business in the new location included
granting loans of 550 million yuan for an oil tank farm project at
the Pudong Airport and the Tianjin Road Project.
</P>
<P>
The bank also relent 45.1 million U.S. dollars in foreign
government loans and export loans for a Huangpu River tunnel
project and an environmental protection project in the Pudong New
Area. It thus became the first commercial bank in China offering
relending services.
</P>
<P>
The building, which was constructed in 1923 and is famous for
both its architecture and functionality, served as the
headquarters of the Shanghai Municipal People's Government after
the founding of the new China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The government office moved in June 1995 to facilitate the
urban reconstruction program designed to restore the Bund's former
glory as a major financial center.
</P>
<P>
The bank plans to undertake an expensive refurbishing program
to transform the building into a modern banking facility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
