<HEADLINE> Rainstorms Damage Ukraine's Crops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 23 (Xinhua) - The rainstorms sweeping across the
middle and western Ukraine are expected to seriously damage the
grain and beet crops of the country this year, said Supikhanov,
the minister of Ariculture-Industry Complexes.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 150,000 hectares of plants had been seriously damaged,
among which 70,000 hectares might face a total crop failure,
estimated Supikhanov when interviewed by Interfax news reporters.
</P>
<P>
Recent natural disasters will most probably smash the
country's targets of producing 35 million tons of grain and 2.5
million tons of beet this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
