<HEADLINE> Hungary's Industry on Upward Track </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Hungary's industrial output was
up 12.9 percent in the first four months of the year, the Ministry
of Industry, Commerce and Tourism said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
As shown by official statistics, the growth was mainly the
result of a 59.4 percent upsurge in the country's machine-building
sector and a 44.8 percent rise in exports.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the four-month period also witnessed a 2.1 percent
increase in domestic industrial sales.
</P>
<P>
Analysts noted that the positive returns followed a 11.1
percent expansion in industrial output, a 1.2 percent decline in
domestic sales and a 34.5 percent boom in exports last year.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's industry was on a downward slope in 1990 through
1992. However, it took an upturn in 1993 and since then has
registered annual growth rates ranging from 4 to 10 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
