<HEADLINE> Italy Advance with 2-1 Victory over Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-DENIS, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Italy advanced into the second
round as group winners after scratching to a 2-1 victory over Austria
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Italian coach Cesare Maldini surprisingly rested Roberto
Baggio who was the key to Italians' victory over Cameroon and
started Alessandro Del Piero.
</P>
<P>
But the Piero-Vieri combination didn't work well in the first
half while at the same time the Austrians fought hard and created
several chances of scoring.
</P>
<P>
After the goalless first half, the Italians took a 1-0 lead at
the 49th minute as Vieri headed home a cross from Piero.
</P>
<P>
The goal also put Viero on top of the scorers' list together
with Argentine striker Batistuta with four goals each.
</P>
<P>
Reborto Baggio replaced Piero at the 73rd minute and his
combination with another second-half substitute Filippo Inzaghi
seemed better.
</P>
<P>
Baggio beat the Austrian off-side trap with a cross which sent
Inzaghi clear. Inzaghi returned the ball to Baggio who made no
mistake in shooting at the 90th minute.
</P>
<P>
Just one minute later, the Austrian team were awarded a penalty
and Andreas Herzog converted the shot from the spot to narrow the
gap to 2-1.
</P>
<P>
The victory put Italy on top of Group B with 7 points. Chile,
which were held by Cameroon to a 1-1 draw, also qualified with 3
points from three draws.
</P>
<P>
Chile will take on Group A leaders Brazil in the round of 16
while Italy play second qualifiers from Group A. 
</P>
</TEXT>
