<HEADLINE> EU Disburses Funds for Research Activities in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- A grant of 4.5 million U.S.
Dollars from the European Union (EU) to finance research and
training activities for small-scale growers has been disbursed to
the cotton and coffee association in Zimbabwe to date, an
official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
EU economic advisor Jose Leandro told the Zimbabwe News Agency
that more money was available for the current financial
difficulty as long as the trust that deals with the issue decided
on the activities to be financed.
</P>
<P>
"We have disbursed most of the money, and we are still waiting
for budgetary requirements for coffee growers," Leandro said.
</P>
<P>
The two boards that represented coffee and cotton growers had
to identify specific training and research activities needed to
be funded for more than 900 small scale farmers.
</P>
<P>
The EU had been funding coffee and cotton activities in
Zimbabwe since 1992. Communal growers are now producing 70
percent of cotton in the country. 
</P>
