<HEADLINE> Chile Reaches Last 16 in World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANTES, France, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Chile reached the last 16 of
the soccer World Cup finals after drawing with Cameroon 1-1 in group B
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Jose Sierra blasted a curvy, booming free kick into the upper right
corner of the goal in the 21st minute to put Chile 1-0 ahead for the
first half.
</P>
<P>
Chile seemed to have their place in the second round secured when
Cameroon was reduced to 10 men after the sending off of Rigobert Song
for his second bookable offence in the 52nd minute.
</P>
<P>
The Indomitable Lions rallied strongly and equalized four minutes
later on a Patrick Mboma header.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon captain Francois Omam Biyik almost scored the winner when
his shot hit the side of the net 16 minutes from time.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon had another player sent off one minute from time when
substitute Lavriano Etame fouled on Salas.
</P>
<P>
Chile finished second in the group with three points and qualified
for the second round along with Italy, who has seven points after
beating Austria 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Austria and Cameroon, both at two points, have been eliminated.
</P>
