<HEADLINE> Congress to Take Over if Government Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 23 (Xinhua) -- A senior leader of Congress said
Tuesday that his party would not hesitate to "discharge its
responsibility" to form a government at the center in the event of
the fall of the government led by the Bharatiya Janata Party
(BJP).
</P>
<P>
"In case the Vajpayee government collapses under its own
weight, Congress party will definitely discharge its
responsibility," Arjun Singh told reporters following a four-hour
meeting of the Congress Working Committee (CWC).
</P>
<P>
Former Indian Prime Minister Chandra Shekhar Monday accused the
BJP-led government of failure on all fronts and asked Congress to
take the initiative to unite all secular forces for the ouster of
the government.
</P>
<P>
Singh, a CWC member, declined to comment on Shekhar's
statement, but he said suggestions made at the CWC meeting for the
formation of an alternative government were noted.
</P>
<P>
Congress has already made its stand clear that it would provide
constructive opposition to the government in matters of national
interests, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We are, however, aware of the fast deteriorating situation in
the country -- political, economic and otherwise," Singh said,
adding that consolidation of secular forces "remains an important
issue for us."
</P>
<P>
Congress would keep a close and constant watch on the
developing situation in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the CWC meeting, Singh said it expressed serious concern
over the rising prices of essential commodities which have caused
acute hardships to the masses.
</P>
<P>
The "government does not seem to have any rational program to
meet the situation," he charged. 
</P>
