<HEADLINE> EU, Israel Hold Talks on Promoting Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) and
Israel Tuesday held talks here on promoting the economy of the
Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
The EU delegation headed by EU Middle East peace envoy
Miguel Moratinos included British Ambassador to Israel David
Anning and other senior EU officials.
</P>
<P>
On the Israeli side, General Director on Economic Affairs of
the Foreign Ministry Victor Harel and some senior officials from
the Labor Ministry and Finance Ministry took part in the talks.
</P>
<P>
During the session, Harel briefed the EU officials on the
latest developments in the Palestinian economy.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the Foreign Ministry, more
Palestinians have been allowed to work in Israel since the
beginning of this year. And the number of Palestinian businessmen
operating in Israel also increased.
</P>
<P>
The EU officials said that they hope Israel would continuously
improve the employment situation for the Palestinian workers and
give more freedom of movement to Palestinian businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has insisted that
the Palestinian economy has been improved after his government
imposed less sanctions against the Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
But the EU argued that the Israeli government should take
more positive measures to lower restrictions on the Palestinian
economy.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Moratinos also briefed the Israeli officials on
his recent visit to Syria, saying that Syria wants to resume
the peace talks with Israel which have been stalled since 1996.
</P>
<P>
But Syria, he noted, insists on its condition that the peace
process between Syria and Israel would be revived only after the
Israeli government accepted the principle of returning the Golan
Heights in exchange for peace. 
</P>
