<HEADLINE> SADC to Increase Fishing Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Southern Africa Development
Community (SADC) has decided that member states should increase
exports of sea products to the third countries for more foreign
currencies.
</P>
<P>
SADC fisheries experts concluded a two-day meeting in
Mauritius Tuesday to prepare for the SADC Fisheries Ministers
Meeting scheduled on Wednesday, according to a communique issued
here Tuesday by the Angolan Ministry of Fisheries.
</P>
<P>
