<HEADLINE> Addis Urges Pressure Put on Asmara </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia Tuesday Called on
the international community to put pressure on Asmara to abide by
the principles of the 1949 Geneva conventions and the additional
protocols which are generally recognized norms of international
law.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the Ethiopian Foreign
Ministry said in a statement that the bombing of an elementary
school by the Eritrean air force in Makele while students were in
their class rooms, killed 51 and wounded 136 others.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the Eritrean authorities have also been
detaining thousands of Ethiopians in camps and expelled well over
4,000 Ethiopian civilians from Eritrea depriving them of their
property.
</P>
<P>
The number of the displaced persons has now reached 143,000
and is expected to increase up to 300,000, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It said, the Eritrean authorities have detained a total of
more than 135,000 tons of dry cargo, 46,741 cubic meters of
liquid cargo and 51 metric tons of asphalt, goods destined for
relief and civilian projects without any legal ground at the
Eritrean ports of Massawa and Assab.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Ethiopian News Agency Tuesday reported that
regions and various sections of the society in the country have
contributed so far over 42 million Birr (6 million U.S Dollars)
in support of the defense force and persons displaced by the war.
</P>
<P>
Data compiled by the agency indicate various regions donated
over 42 million Birr (6 million U.S. Dollars) up until June 22
and the figure does not include the salary pledged by civil
servants, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
