<HEADLINE> Cameroon Coach Says Disallowed Goal Good </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANTES, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Cameroon coach Claude Leroy on Tuesday
said the disallowed goal by Francois Omam Biyick was a good one.
</P>
<P>
"I've seen the replay; there wasn't even a shadow of a foul on that
goal. Francois Omam Biyick's goal was a good one. Players are shocked.
We would accept being eliminated, but not like that," said the coach
after their 1-1 draw with Chile.
</P>
<P>
He added, "It has been a two-month long adventure. The team has
been great. They played really well against Austria. It's a shame they
scored a goal towards the end."
</P>
<P>
The Frenchman said, "This has been a tremendous World Cup,
organized in an excellent way... We must let bygones be bygones. It's
the end of the road for me here."
</P>
<P>
He said he would quit the coaching job at Cameroon and work at the
Strasbourg Racing Club in France. 
</P>
