<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Massive landslides have buried
and killed at least 43 villagers in a hilly region in Lichuan
County, East China's Jiangxi Province, as a result of flooding.
</P>
<P>
The landslides, which occurred on June 22, have also injured
over 100 people and destroyed 500 houses. More than 20 people
are still missing.
</P>
