<HEADLINE> Floods Hit Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Severe floods have hit Southwest
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in the past two days,
with the scenic city of Guilin hardest affected in about 49 years.
</P>
<P>
Many city districts and rural houses were inundated and
landslides and mud and stone flows were caused.
</P>
<P>
Guilin saw the flood peak in its section of the Guijiang River
2.7 meters above the danger level and the flood peaks in Wuzhou
and Liuzhou cities rise above their danger levels by 8.2 meters
and one meters respectively.
</P>
<P>
The floods arrived after two days of torrential rain. More rain
is expected tomorrow. 
</P>
