<HEADLINE> Zhuhai-Macao Bridge Scheduled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a bridge linking
Zhuhai of south China's Guangdong Province with neighboring Macao
is scheduled to start on June 29, an official of the Hongkong and
Macao Affairs Office of the State Council said here today.
</P>
<P>
Xie Houhe, director of the office's Macao affairs department,
who is also in charge of the Sino-Portuguese co-ordinating group
for large-scale capital construction, said that the important
bridge -- the second land passage between Macao and the mainland
-- has been named Lotus Bridge after a group discussion.
</P>
<P>
Lotus is a component of the Macao Special Administrative
Region's flag and emblem's design, as well as one of Macao's
symbols.
</P>
<P>
The Gongbei Customs now serves as the only passageway between
Macao and the mainland, and is often crowded with customers as
trade and economic exchanges there increase.
</P>
<P>
The bridge is designed to be 1,500 meters long and 22 meter
high, with six traffic lanes. It will be built at a cost of 200
million yuan and completed by the end of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
