<HEADLINE> HKTA to Make Most of New Airport Opening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Tourist
Association (HKTA) has taken a number of measures to promote Hong
Kong and maximize the opportunities offered by the July 6 opening
of the new Hong Kong International Airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA has invited more than 120 members of the international
media and some 200 members of the travel trade from around the
world on familiarization visits on various dates coinciding with,
or falling just after, the new airport opening, the HKTA said in a
press release Wednesday. Special tours of Hong Kong will also be
arranged.
</P>
<P>
The new airport site has long been a key element of such
visits, with more than 700 members of the media and 350
representatives of the travel trade worldwide having visited the
site at various stages of its construction.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA is preparing special commemorative certificates to
present to each member of such groups.
</P>
<P>
In cooperation with the travel trade both here and overseas,
the HKTA has also helped put together special tours whose
participants will enter Hong Kong via the Kai Tak Airport now in
use and leave via the new airport which begins operation on July
6.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-based Cathay Pacific Airways and the Airport
Authority are also planning to present souvenirs to incoming
passengers during the opening period.
</P>
<P>
More HKTA information counters will be set up at the new
airport with longer business hours.
</P>
<P>
And some 75 TouristInfo "Powerphones" are to be installed
inside the Arrivals Hall.
</P>
<P>
A multilingual communication guide will be distributed to local
taxi-drivers to facilitate communication between them and their
passengers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
