<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Collect More Fees from Industrial Polluters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- China's environment watchdog has
decided to levy more fees upon industrial polluters to raise funds
for pollution control facilities.
</P>
<P>
The fee-collecting standard will be raised higher than average
cost of treatment of industrial wastes. Enterprises will get
policy and financial supports from the government in controling
pollution, according to Xie Zhenhua, director of the State
Environmental Protection Administration.
</P>
<P>
Pollution fees paid by enterprises are a major source of the
450 billion yuan, the total investment planned for the country's
pollution-control work in the 1996-2000 period, Xie told a news
conference held by the Information Office of the State Council
today.
</P>
<P>
Areas in 27 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities,
which are responsible for overproduction of sulphur dioxide and
for related acid rain, will have to pay a special fee, he
announced.
</P>
<P>
China plans to build 52 waste water treatment plants along the
seriously-polluted Huaihe River in the next three years at a cost
of more than five billion yuan (602 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
More funds are needed for pollution control facilities in the
Liaohe and Haihe rivers, and the Taihu, Dianchi and Chaohu lakes,
also the key polluted areas in China.
</P>
<P>
The government and banks will provide part of the funds, but
enterprises must pay too, said Xie.
</P>
<P>
He added that China is to attract more overseas loans in this
field, even though it has got over two billion US dollars as a
result of a program which aims to seek four billion US dollars of
foreign loans before 2000.
</P>
<P>
"Foreign investors will have more opportunities to directly
invest in China's environmental protection market, and will be
surely benefited," Xie said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980624.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Urges Devotion to Modernization Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The great cause of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics provides a vast arena for
young people of all ethnic groups to fully exhibit their
competence, according to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, also
general secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks today during a meeting with the new
leadership of the Communist Youth League of China and some
deputies to the 14th National Congress of the CYL which closed on
Tuesday. The leadership and some 60 deputies representing the
nation's 56 ethnic groups attended the meeting at Zhongnanhai,
headquarters of both the government and CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Party has always attached great importance to the younger
generation and regards them as the future of the motherland and
the hope of the Chinese nation. Generations of young people
through different periods have contributed greatly to the Chinese
nation and the the magnificent history of the Party in the 20th
century. The younger generation has been entrusted with a mission
to bring China into the 21st century and write an even more
magnificent song of youth, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"China will basically have traqsformed itself into a modern
powerful, democratic, and civilized socialist country by the
middle of the next century. You will be my age when that
happens. As youngsters, we participated in the struggle to
overthrow the reactionary rule and worked for the founding of New
China under the leadership of the Party. Chinese youth of today
are also striving for the realization of the modernization
blueprint," according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Young people should cultivate lofty ideals and firm convictions
in the process of building the country and revitalizing the
Chinese nation, said Jiang. He called Chinese youth to adhere to
the Party's basic theory and basic line in following the socialist
road with Chinese characteristics, and to volunteer to work under
difficult conditions.
</P>
<P>
"Competition amongst nations is virtually competition for
professionals and the ability to create new things. You should
continue to learn while in your prime time," said Jiang, adding
that the prosperity of youth to a great extent means the
prosperity of the nation. Therefore, the Party and the public as a
whole should exhibit great concern for the healthy development of
young people who will safeguard China's long-term stability and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The league's new leaders and various deputies reported on their
work and life, with a number of deputies inviting the general
secretary to visit their hometowns.
</P>
<P>
Vice-President Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing Committee of
the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, presided over
the meeting.  
</P>
