<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 13:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq, Iran Reach Agreement on POWs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Iraq and Iran reached an agreement
here Wednesday to settle the issue of Prisoners of War (POWs)
between the two countries, the Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported.
</P>
<P>
A source at the Iraqi Foreign Ministry told the INA that under
the memorandum of understanding, Iraq and Iran will cooperate to
ensure smooth implementation of a mechanism which will bring about
a final and quick solution for the exchange of POWs and detainees
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The source said the two sides held a series of in-depth and
constructive talks here last week, which led to the sealing of the
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will meet again at border cities to implement the
agreement, the source added.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Iran recently stepped up their efforts to resolve the
issue of POWs, which has been preventing the two countries from
resuming normal relations since the end of their eight-year war in
1988.
</P>
<P>
In April this year, the two countries carried out the largest
round of repatriation of POWs and detainees since 1991, in which
Iran released nearly 6,000 Iraqi POWs and Iraq in return set free
about 400 Iranian POWs and civilian detainees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
