<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guilin Today (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Industries closely associated with tourism, including the
transportation and telecommunications sectors, are witnessing
rapid development.
</P>
<P>
Guilin's new Liangjiang International Airport has annual
handling capacity of five million passengers.
</P>
<P>
Program-controlled telephone lines and cellular phone networks
link the city with countries and regions throughout the world,
with the city offering express mail services to 130 countries.
</P>
<P>
The city has achieved coordinated development in numerous
areas, including the environmental protection, industry,
agriculture, high-tech and foreign trade sectors.
</P>
<P>
Some 49 heavily polluting factories and mills have been closed
in recent years, and the city has opened four wastewater treatment
centers and a network of garbage transfer stations.
</P>
<P>
A special treatment program has transformed the Lijiang River
into one of the world's best protected urban rivers.
</P>
<P>
Guilin's per capita public landscaped area stands at 6.1 sq.m.,
with greenery covering 35.8 percent of the city's total area.
</P>
<P>
Tourism has created extensive business opportunities in the
city, with official statistics through the end of last year
showing that the local government had approved 754 foreign-funded
projects involving total investments of over two billion
U.S. dollars. Guilin also recorded a 1997 foreign trade volume of
200 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The citizens of Guilin have enjoyed a constantly improved
quality of life. Some 54,000 technicians currently work in 14
institutions of higher education, 22 research institutes, and
eight product examination and analysis centers.
</P>
<P>
The Guilin High-Tech Industrial Development Zone was
established in 1982 and is currently home to over 500
businesses. The zone's total income for 1997 hit 2.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show Guilin has achieved an annual economic growth
of 15 percent for the past few years, with last year's GDP hitting
10.5 billion yuan last year, up 18.8 percent on the previous
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
