<HEADLINE> US Electronics Leader to Invest More in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- US Seagate Technology, a world
electronics leader, will increase its investment in Shenzhen, a
special economic zone in south China, to 122 million US dollars in
three to five years, from 20 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A contract on increasing assests for Shenzhen Seagate
Co. Ltd. was signed today at the Great Hall of the People. This is
one of the important Sino-US economic cooperation programs signed
on the eve of US President Bill Clinton's visit to China.
</P>
<P>
The increased investment will be used mainly to purchase
production equipment and related facilities.
</P>
<P>
US Seagate Technology and China Electronic Industrial
Corporation jointly set up Shenzhen Seagate Co. Ltd. in 1992. The
joint venture, with about 1,700 employees, has turned out more
than 16 million hard discs, thus being regarded as one of the most
efficient subsidiary of Seagate.
</P>
<P>
Seagate is very confident about China's macro-economic
environment and expansion of its own business in the country, said
an official with Seagate, who added that more investment will
still be poured into another hard disc producer invested by
Seagate in Wuxi, a city in east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Global sales of Seagate surpassed nine billion US dollars in
1997. Shenzhen Seagate took the lead in China's foreign-funded
enterprises in exporting nearly 940 million US dollars worth-of
products last year.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from the State Development Planning Commission
and Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation attended
today's signing ceremony.  
</P>
