<HEADLINE> New Honors, Awards System for HK Disciplined Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) government announced Wednesday a new
system of honors and awards for the disciplined services.
</P>
<P>
The new system will give recognition to meritorious and long
service rendered by officers of five major disciplined services,
namely, police, fire services, immigration service, customs and
excise, and correctional services.
</P>
<P>
Principal Assistant Secretary for Security Philip Chan said:
"Honors and awards are conducive to the maintenance of morale of
the disciplined services."
</P>
<P>
The new system comprises three categories -- Distinguished
Service Medal for directorate officers, Meritorious Service Medal
for officers of all ranks, and Long Service Medals and Clasps for
officers who have completed certain years of satisfactory service.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of distinguished and meritorious service awards
will be announced in early July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
