<HEADLINE> China Improving Rural Credit Cooperatives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China has
started pilot projects in 10 counties to improve rural credit
cooperatives to reduce financial risks.
</P>
<P>
Bank sources say that this will give the rural credit
cooperatives more standardized management that is more
cooperative. Insolvent cooperatives and those greatly at risk will
be corrected.
</P>
<P>
The move will also improve cooperatives' business systems,
financial supervision, internal controls, and agricultural
services.
</P>
<P>
Rural credit cooperatives have a more than 50-year history in
China and have provided reliable support for agriculture, rural
economic development, and rural household development.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, there were 50,000 of them, with a trillion
yuan in savings deposits and 727.3 billion yuan in loans.
</P>
