<HEADLINE> Tanzania Welcomes Investment in Dams Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania expressed its
welcome to foreign and private investment in building power
generation dams on four major rivers to ease the acute shortage
of power across the country.
</P>
<P>
Manju Msambya, Deputy Minister of Energy and Minerals, told
the on-going parliamentary session in the new capital city of
Dodoma Tuesday that dams are needed on the rivers of Malagarasi,
Mara, Rufiji and Ruvuma to support the two hydro-power plants on
rivers of Mtera and Kidatu which face frequent water shortages.
</P>
<P>
Local media Wednesday quoted the deputy minister as saying
that while concentrated on building dams on five other rivers,
the Tanzanian government is currently unable to carry out the
four projects due to financial constraints.
</P>
<P>
"The government will conclude five hydro-power plants on the
rivers of Lower Kihansi, Upper Kihausi, Masigira, Rumakali and
Ruhudji proposed to end in the year 2010 in accordance with a
Power Master Plan," said Msambya. 
