<HEADLINE> China Keeps Major Telephone Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The telecommunications industry
is one of the fastest growing sectors in China, which is expecting
at least 100 million individual customers this year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, there were almost 93 million customers and
that figure was growing at a rate of 77,000 daily, a government
telecoms official said at the 7th China International Electronics
and Telecommunications Exhibition which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
There are now 11 phones for every 100 people and one per
household in urban districts, and the state plans to spend 150
billion yuan on telecommunications this year.
</P>
<P>
The number of mobile phone users increased by 3.48 million in
the first four months of this year, up 170 percent from the same
period of last year and bringing the total number in China to 16.7
million, making it third in the world. The official predicts that
number to increase at an annual rate of 10 million to 40 million
by 2000. China's GSM network is connected to 23 countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
The four-day exhibition has attracted exhibitors from 14
countries and regions, showing the latest computer network
technology, multimedia systems, and satellite and mobile
telecommunications.  
</P>
