<HEADLINE> Security Men at Lagos Airport Ordered to Shoot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Security guards at the
international airport in Lagos have been authorized to shoot at
sight the persons found at the location of sensitive aviation
facilities, especially at night.
</P>
<P>
The instruction, which has already come into effect, followed
the recent theft of reflectors of the antenna of the Instrument
Landing System (ILS) acquired by the Federal Airports Authority
of Nigeria (FAAN) in April, the Post Express reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, armed escorts now accompany technicians and
engineers to the installation site of the ILS, while security men
guarding the facilities are, henceforth, to be pre-informed of
the movement of such FAAN staff to the location to avoid
accidental deaths.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, more security personnel have been
deployed to protect the landing aids while all units have been
placed at alert to monitor and provide 24-hour surveillance at
the nation's gateway. 
</P>
