<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Wednesday in quiet trading
after tracking the local currency which declined on the back of a
weaker yen.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index shed 1.88
points to 455.37, the all-share Emas Index eased 0.92 points to
116.50, the Industrial Index was 1.57 points lower at 899.14 and
the Second Board Index erased 0.98 of a point to 99.87.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 342 to 161 while 189 counters were
unchanged and 229 untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 92.673 million shares worth 179.419
million ringgit (45.537 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board volume rose to 88.406 million shares valued at
173.181 million ringgit (43.954 million dollars) from 78.916
million shares worth 159.703 million ringgit (40.533 million
dollars) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board volume declined marginally to 4.267 million
shares valued at 6.238 million ringgit (1.583 million dollars)
from Tuesday's 4.363 million shares worth 7.815 million ringgit
(1.983 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals increased to 12.467 million shares valued at
9.819 million ringgit (2.492 million dollars) from 1.356 million
shares worth 4.058 million ringgit (1.029 million dollars)
Tuesday.
