<DOCNO> XIE19980624.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Says Social Science Academy Needs To Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Li Tieying, the new president of
the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, says that the academy's
research facilities should be improved in two or three years and
there should be more housing for researchers.
</P>
<P>
Li said the academy should have the highest level of social
science inquiry in the country to deal with problems in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
The CASS, which was set up in 1977, has become the country's
ideology and theory center. Its 30 or so institutes have close
relations with academics outside China, but it is not seen as a
modern research institute of the electronic age and its 3,000
researchers do not get high salaries, and the housing problem is
acute.
</P>
<P>
Li, who replaced Hu Sheng as the CASS's president in March,
explained, "I come to provide logistic support for the academy."
He conveyed President Jiang Zemin's greetings to both researchers
and workers, and said that Jiang has mentioned the importance of
theoretical work repeatedly.
</P>
<P>
"It is impossible for a big Party like the Communist Party of
China and a big country like China to reach its goals of
invigorating the country without the guidance of correct theory,"
Li said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders have said that CASS should assist and advise
the Party and the government, especially in economic matters and
policy making, and Li reveals that the central government has said
that a still better CASS required to be built, and he asked
researchers to complete more research projects this year, and that
more computers be installed and a new data base and a library be
built. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
