<DOCNO> XIE19980624.0173 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Korea, Japan to Hold Meeting on Security Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea and Japan will hold a
consultative meeting over Japan's military role in Northeast Asia
region on Friday, said South Korea's Ministry of Foreign Affairs
and Trade Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We can not sit idly by watching Japan expand its military role
which could infringe upon the South Korean sovereignty," said Moon
Bong-joo, director of the ministry's Asia Pacific Affairs Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Japan has expanded its military power as a revised defense
cooperation agreement signed by the United States and Japan allows the
Japanese troops to assist the U.S. army in case of emergency in the
Northeast Asian region.
</P>
<P>
At the first meeting on security issue in history, South Korea
is to ask for a pledge that the revised agreement will not violate
its sovereignty when the United States and Japan cooperate in case
of emergency.
</P>
<P>
"We decided to accept the proposal by Japan to hold the
consultative meeting on security, despite public sentiment against
Japan's past militarism. We though it is the right time to
establish a direct bilateral mechanism on security issues
involving the two nations, " said Moon.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Japan is expected to confer with South Korea
over emergency case in the Korean peninsula as problems there will
influence Japan.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts said South Korea expects the meeting will help
the establishment of the Northeast Asia Security Dialogue, a
regional multilateral security forum consisting of South Korea, the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, the United States, China.
Russia and Japan. Seoul proposed to set up the forum in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
