<HEADLINE> Security Tightened in Central Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Security measures in Matale town
in the Central province of Sri Lanka have been tightened following
the disclosure by two arrested Tamil rebels that they had
earmarked key establishments for planting bombs, according to
police Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Investigations have led to the discovery of a map of Matale
town in their possession, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
It had indicated that they were targeting some of the key
installations in the Matale district including the police station,
telecom facility, a kerosene storage tank and a transformer
complex.
</P>
<P>
It was revealed during the investigations that the two arrested
women rebels had made several trips to Matale town from Batticaloa
in the past couple of weeks, studying the location of
installations they had in mind for their mission, the sources
noted.
</P>
<P>
Adequate steps have now been taken to protect all vital
installations in the district, said the sources, adding that the
assistance of the security forces too has been sought in this
connection. 
</P>
