baggage, and food services.
</P>
<P>
Many other European companies have been putting their money,
advanced technology, and experience to work in China. By the end
of 1997, the European Union had backed 8,352 projects in China,
with 13 billion U.S. dollars worth of paid-in investment.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that great business opportunities will come as
China's investment conditions improve with political stability,
and fast economic growth.
</P>
<P>
At the '98 Sino-European economic and trade fair in Brussels in
mid-June, officials and business people discussed European
companies' investment experiences in China and China's overseas
investment policies. It also held investment promotion activities
for agriculture, the chemical industry, energy, and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The EU and Shanghai government jointly financed the
Sino-European International Business College three years ago in
Shanghai, to graduate 310 MBAs annually, and offer short-term
training courses to 2,000 senior administrators. 
</P>
