<HEADLINE> U.S. Firms Invest Most in Shanghai's Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Companies from the United States
have made the largest investment in the Pudong New Area, a
flourishing trade and financial district of this economic center
of China.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that 302 U.S. companies have registered
in Pudong, with the total investment hitting 4.44 billion
U.S. dollars, the largest among investors from more than 60
countries.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, U.S. companies accounted for 5.8 percent
of the number of overseas firms with investments in Pudong and 18
percent of all overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. companies invest an average of 14.7 million
U.S. dollars in Pudong, with two investing more than 1 billion
U.S. dollars each. Thirty percent of the 80 multinational
corporations in Pudong are from the United States.
</P>
<P>
U.S. companies invest mainly in automobiles and auto parts,
fine chemicals, precision instruments, household electrical
appliances, energy and power, telecommunications, and
environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Citibank and America Insurance Group are among the first
overseas financial institutions in Pudong, where U.S. companies
also have a significant presence in the service and trade
sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
