<HEADLINE> Nepali Currency Falls to Record Low Against Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali rupee fell further
against the U.S. dollar by 0.40 rupee to a record low of 68.00
rupees for a U.S. dollar on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Nepal Rastra Bank, the country's central bank, on Wednesday
refixed the buying and selling rates of the rupee against the
dollar at 68.00 and 68.65 respectively from Tuesday's 67.60 and
68.25.
</P>
<P>
The latest fluctuation of the Nepali rupee came after the
Indian rupee, to which the Nepali rupee is pegged, hit a new low
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After maintaining stability for three months by mid-May, the
Nepali rupee has weakened against the dollar by 4.30 rupees since
then.
</P>
<P>
As the Indian rupee keeps sliding over the international
economic sanctions following India's nuclear tests last month, the
Nepali currency, pegged to the Indian currency at a fixed rate of
1.6:1, has to follow suit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
