<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh PM Arrives in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister of Bangladesh
Sheikh Hasina arrived here Wednesday morning on a day-long visit
to Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Hasina is the first prime minister to visit Pakistan after the
country conducted nuclear tests in May. She was received by
Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif at the airport.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi prime minister is visiting Pakistan after a
meeting with Indian Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee in New
Delhi last week.
</P>
<P>
She has expressed her desire to play a mediatory role to reduce
tension between Pakistan and India and establish peace in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Her visit to Pakistan is regarded as part of the diplomatic
efforts to reduce tension between Pakistan and India following
their nuclear explosions.
</P>
<P>
During her stay here, Hasina will hold a meeting with Nawaz
Sharif to discuss bilateral and regional issues. She will also
call on Pakistani President Rafiq Tarar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
