<HEADLINE> "People's Daily": Raising Standards of Using Overseas Investment (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- "People's Daily," China's leading
national newspaper, today runs a full page publishing a group of
summary articles calling for opening wider and raising the level
of using overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
These articles are based on speeches delivered by leaders of
ministries, central government departments, officials from
Shanghai and Hubei, an executive from SINOPEC and a foreign trade
researcher. The speeches were part of a recent forum on further
increasing the standards for using overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Peiyan, minister in charge of the State Development
Planning Commission, said in his speech that, under the current
situation, breakthroughs should be made in the use of overseas
investment in the service sector, in reforming the state-owned
enterprises and in developing the private business economy, and in
the central and western areas of China. More multinationals should
also be attracted to invest in China, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meng Xiangang, deputy secretary-general of the State Economic
and Trade Commission, called for the successful operation of
existing overseas-financed businesses in China by means of
improving the investment environment and giving a helping hand in
resolving difficulties and problems in production or operations
faced by overseas enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Wan Baorui, vice-minister of agriculture, urged a
successful use of overseas investment in developing China's
farming sector, while Hu Xijie, vice-minister of communications,
said that utilizing overseas investment in an active, rational and
efficient manner is important to the country's transportation
infrastructure.
</P>
</TEXT>
