<HEADLINE> "People's Daily": Raising Standards of Using Overseas Investment (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of foreign trade and
economic cooperation, noted that his ministry would intensify
overseas investment promotion programs, improve the industrial
structure of overseas investment, open wider China's service
sector still and implement policies to encourage more overseas
investment in China's central and western areas so as to keep the
volume of overseas investment at a constant level this year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Yiren, vice-mayor of Shanghai, pledged that his city
would open more areas to overseas investors, while Deng Daokun,
vice-governor of central China's Hubei Province, said his province
would speed up the pace of overseas funding by encouraging
investment in agriculture, infrastructure and the revitalization
of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
