Petrochemical Corp. (SINOPEC), said his group would pay great
attention to the study of changes in the use of overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, China had approved 312,174 overseas-financed
businesses, with contracts involving a use of 538.675 billion
U.S. dollars of investment from overseas and actual paid-in
overseas investment of 236.756 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total approved overseas-backed businesses, 7,308
were added in the first five months of this year, down by 7.33
percent as compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The contractual use of overseas investment in the newly
approved overseas businesses amounted to 17.511 billion
U.S. dollars, up 3.46 percent compared to last year, while the
paid-in volume of overseas investment during the January-May
period this year was 14.885 billion U.S. dollars, a drop of 1.49
percent over last year.  
