<HEADLINE> China Standardizes Retail Outlet Classification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has
worked out standards for the classification of retail outlets to
standardize market practices.
</P>
<P>
According to a document of the State Internal Trade Bureau,
retail outlets will be divided into eight types: department
stores, supermarkets, large-scale comprehensive supermarkets,
convenience shops, warehouse stores, shops for special products,
boutiques and shopping centers.
</P>
<P>
The retail sector has flourished in an unprecedented manner in
recent years. However, due to a lack of regulations, the naming of
retail outlets has not been up to standards, bureau officials said.
</P>
<P>
The projected standards will provide references for retail
developers to choose the type of business they want to engage in,
bureau officials said. 
</P>
