<HEADLINE> Rugova Sets Conditions for Kosovo Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Kosovo's ethnic Albanian leader
Ibrahim Rugova said Tuesday that negotiations on Kosovo would not
start until Yugoslav authorities satisfied conditions set by the
six-nation Contact Group.
</P>
<P>
Rugova made the remark while meeting with U.S. special envoy
Richard Holbrooke at the U.S. Embassy in the Macedonian capital of
Skopje. Rugova is on his way to Belgium for a visit.
