<HEADLINE> Detroit Shock Beats Sacramento Monarchs in WNBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Detroit Shock beat Sacramento
Monarchs 61-57 to win its second straight victory in a WNBA game
Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Korie Hlede scored 18 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the
Shock while Linda Burgess led the Monarchs with 13 points.
</P>
<P>
Sacramento trailed 31-22 at the half time and by as many as 13
early in the second. Franthea Price hit two 3-pointers to pull the
Monarchs within 44-39 with 10 minutes left.
</P>
<P>
But Detroit increased the gap to nine points with 5:30 minutes
remaining. The Monarchs answered with an 8-2 run to narrow the
score 52-49.
</P>
<P>
But Price's 3-point attempt bounced off the rim, and Cindy
Brown grabbed the rebound, then hit three of four free throws to
clinch the game.
</P>
<P>
In another game played today in New York, the New York Liberty
edged the Cleveland Rockers 59-57.
</P>
<P>
Kym Hampton's layup with five seconds to go sealed the
victory. Vickie Johnson had 27 points on 12-of-16 shooting. The
rest of the team was 8-for-30 in the game.
</P>
<P>
The Rockers were playing their second game in as many nights
without point guard Suzie McConnell Serio, who leads the WNBA in
assists and is second in steals. She injured her right foot.
</P>
<P>
Rushia Brown led the Rockers with 12 points, while Eva Nemcova
and Fijalkowski had 11 each. 
</P>
