<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Chinese wigs are
available in France to add color to football fans coming from all
over the world to watch the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
The 5,000 colorful wigs, worth about 24.5 U.S. dollars each,
were transported from a township in east China's Jiangsu
Province to France just before the opening of the big football
event.
</P>
<P>
Designers at a wig factory in Huai'an city of Jiangsu
came up with the idea of providing wigs to World Cup fans who
usually seek unusual looks, and offered sample wigs to French
businessmen in March, according to a Shanghai-based newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Some 500,000 yuan (about 60,000 U.S. dollars) was invested by
French wholesalers in the factory soon after they decided to order
5,000 wigs, worth one million yuan (120,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A Chinese expert said wigs are considered a light-industry
product, which often appears on China's export list. But this is
the first year they are being sold at the World Cup.  
</P>
