<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Venezuelan government is
working with the Interamerican Development Bank in an effort to
obtain a loan of one to 1.5 billion U.S. dollars to help ease its
financial difficulty.
</P>
<P>
The expected loan, if available, will be used to help reduce
the nation's fiscal deficit to 2.5 percent of its gross domestic
product (GDP).
</P>
