<P>
Milosevic and U.S. envoy, Richard Holbrooke, held talks later,
both agreeing to settle the Kosovo issue by political means and in
a peaceful way.
</P>
<P>
Holbrooke did not release any details of the meeting, only
saying that the Kosovo crisis was at a critical moment.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. envoy will leave for Pristina, Kosovo, on Wednesday
and meet ethnic Albanian leaders there. He is to return to
Belgrade Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
