<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 3.8 Million Illegal Land-use Cases Found Nationwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 24 (Xinhua) -- The State Land Administration
under the Ministry of Land and Natural Resources has discovered
more than 3.82 million cases of illegal land use across the
country, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last October, nearly 55 percent of the cases had
been dealt with, but about 1.7 million remain unresolved.
</P>
<P>
The administration recently made public two cases which have
been handled in a move to publicize their land use campaign in a
country where arable land is in critically short supply.
</P>
<P>
Between 1992 and 1995, the Chengdu municipal government in
Sichuan province overstepped its authority in examing
and approving 244 projects. The projects took up 4,038 hectares of
land, 66 percent of which are arable land.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 244 projects, one should have been approved by the
State Council, while the others should have been approved by
the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
The other case made public by the ministry involves a Beijing
developer.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the Beijing Changxinghuilong Villa Co Ltd illegally
occupied 38 hectares of land, 73 percent of which are arable land,
in northwestern Beijing. The company planned to construct villas
and apartments and other buildings for commercial use.  
</P>
</TEXT>
