<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis, Novotna Sail into Second Round at Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The world's top woman player
Martina Hingis of Switzerland and Czech veteran Jana Novotna
sailed into the second round of the on-going Wimbledon Tennis
championships after beating their opponents in straight sets.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Hingis, who became the youngest player to
win a Wimbledon title in 1997, started her journey to defend her
honor with a difficult spell.
</P>
<P>
American challenger Lisa Raymond, who ranked 19th in the world
and once defeated Hingis last year, put up a brillant fight
against the 17-year world number one and only marginally lost the
first set by 5-7.
</P>
<P>
After a long spell of rain delay, Hingis restored her usual
smashing style of pin point accuracy and snatched the winning set
by 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Novotna, last year's runner-up, gave her opponent no
chance of resistance by winning the two sets 6-3, 6-3. Seventh
seed American Venus Williams also followed their steps into the
next stage by beating Canada's Jana Nejedly 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Due to frequent invasion of rain spells, most of the men's
first round matches failed to take place. Australian Patrick
Rafter, who ranked 6th in this tournament, ousted Ivo Heuberger of
Switzerland 6-1, 6-2, 4-6, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
The 4th seed Greg Rusedski of Britain was trailing his little
known qualifier opponent by one set when the play was abandoned
due to falling rain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
