<HEADLINE> "Morocco Deserve to Qualify", Says Michel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Morocco coach Henri Michel
said he thought his team deserved to qualify.
</P>
<P>
Morocco was eliminated from the World Cup despite a 3-0 win over
Scotland on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"It's the worst scenario we could think of. We had a great
match, scored great goals but it's all over. I'm very sad for the
players. They would have deserved to go through." said Michel.
</P>
<P>
Scottish coach Craig Brown was also disappointed as his team
maintained their sad record of never getting past the group stage of
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Brown said he was disappointed for the team and the travelling
fans.
</P>
<P>
"You can't give goals away at this level. We were reduced to 10
men but we were already behind at that point." Brown said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
