<HEADLINE> Coach Olsen Says Victory Incredible </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MARSEILLE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Norway coach Egil Olsen said on
Tuesday their 2-1 win over world champions Brazil was "incredible".
</P>
<P>
"It's incredible. I didn't believe this can happen. At least there
will one more match when I'm in charge," said Olsen.
</P>
<P>
He added, "I'm not only pleased but very, very proud. It's quite
amazing what happened. We started very low key but when we heard the
score of the other match, we had to change and take more risks. And
you saw what happened."
</P>
<P>
If Norway had drawn or lost, Morocco would have advanced with a 3-0
win over Scotland.
</P>
<P>
Olsen said, "I've already started to think about the Italy match.
We must recover fast and prepare quickly. We must not get carried away
with this win."
</P>
<P>
Norway's opponent in the second round will be former world champion
Italy.
</P>
<P>
Olsen gave much credit to Brazil, who also lost to Norway in their
last encounter in May last year.
</P>
<P>
"I was deeply impressed by Brazil. They're very, very good with the
ball and although of course the game was less important for them. I
though they were excellent and can go a very long way indeed," Olsen
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
