<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Morocco Win but Eliminated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
SAINT-ETIENNE, June 23 (Xinhua) -- Morocco scored their first
win at the France'98 World Cup finals but still could not avoid the
fate of being eliminated.
</P>
<P>
Morocco trounced Scotland 3-0 in a Group A match but their hope
of qualifying for the second round was dashed by a late Norway
penalty shot in the other match of the group played at Marseille.
</P>
<P>
Norway came from behind to beat title-holders Brazil 2-1 to
qualify as the runners-up of Group A.
</P>
<P>
In the match both Morocco and Scotland must win to keep their
hope of qualifying alive, Morocco dominated the match with an early
goal at the 22nd minute from Abdejilil Bassir beat Scotland
goal-keeper Jim Leighton with a first-time drive.
</P>
<P>
Just one minute into the second half, Abdejilil Hadda sprinted
past Davd Weir and hit the ball into the net.
</P>
<P>
Craig Burley was shown the red card after the 53rd minute for a
clumsp challenge on Bassir.
</P>
<P>
Morocco took the numerical advantage to control the midfield. At
the 82nd minute, Bassir's shot was deflected past Leighton by Colin
Hendry and Morocco chalked away the 3-0 victory.
</P>
<P>
But the big-margin victory was not enough for the Moroccan to
gain a berth in the round of 16 as Norway surprisingly beat Brazil
2-1 thanks to a penalty shot at the 89th minute.
</P>
<P>
Norway garnered 5 points from two draws and one win. It was
their second win over Brazil in two years.
</P>
<P>
For the Scottish team, they again failed to get through to the
second round in World Cup finals. Their seven previous World Cup
trips all ended in the group stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
