<HEADLINE> Jordan's Parliament Criticizes Israel's Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Jordanian National Assembly
(Parliament) Tuesday accused Israel of killing the Middle East
peace process by endorsing a plan to expand the authority of
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian Parliament said in a statement that Israel's
decision has reflected its intentions to kill every effort exerted
by all the concerned parties to achieve a just, comprehensive and
lasting peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli Cabinet Sunday approved the plan to set up an
"umbrella authority" for Jerusalem over eight West Bank Jewish
settlements to the east, north and south of the city.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements signed between the Palestinians and
Israel, the issue of Jerusalem will be negotiated in the final
status talks for a permanent peace agreement. Neither side should
take unilateral actions to change the status of the city.
</P>
<P>
Israel's decision is an act of "open aggression" and should be
"firmly confronted," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian parliament called on all the peace-loving
countries and organizations in the world to resist Israel's plan
by all possible means.
</P>
<P>
Israel occupied the traditionally Arab East Jerusalem in the
1967 Mideast War, which the Palestinians want as the capital of
their future independent state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
